I'm in agreement with your suggestion that the user interface should
maintain a profile of users and what they type, but I think your idea
is a bit complex from the implementation view. 

I think it would be simpler for user interfaces to maintain user-definable
tables, which the user could set up once and amend as he/she needs.
Why not have something that translates MC to MC.MIT.EDU for a given user.
Maybe someone else would like MC to be MCLELLAN.COM? I personally would
like my personal workstation to be named JSOL, but of course in the
domain scheme it will be JSOL.BBN.COM. I should still be able to say
TELNET JSOL from my site and have it work (then again I don't think
anyone is arguing against that).

I guess there are several ways to allow nicknames under the domain
system.

